data.title: King Kold Karnival - Alpha Tau Omega, 1959
meta_keywords: Universities & colleges -- North Dakota -- Grand Forks
data.meta_description: Alpha Tau Omega Fraternity's snow sculpture for the King Kold Karnival. The sculpture depicts a UND hockey player scoring a goal while the bunny referee is distracted. The slogan in the snow reads: "Sioux score Nine While Ref Makes Time." The winter festival known as the King Kold Karnival was a staple at UND from 1951-1968. The event usually included contests, sled races, dances, beauty pageants, and most notably large snow sculptures. A brief resurgence emerged in 1979 but was not continued.
data.text:
Description

Alpha Tau Omega Fraternity's snow sculpture for the King Kold Karnival. The sculpture depicts a UND hockey player scoring a goal while the bunny referee is distracted. The slogan in the snow reads: "Sioux score Nine While Ref Makes Time." The winter festival known as the King Kold Karnival was a staple at UND from 1951-1968. The event usually included contests, sled races, dances, beauty pageants, and most notably large snow sculptures. A brief resurgence emerged in 1979 but was not continued.
